### Optional validation (recommended)

Add a helper to ensure end time is after start time when both are provided:

```java
private void validateTiming(String start, String end) {
    if (start == null || end == null) return;
    // Parse HH:mm
    String[] s = start.split(":");
    String[] e = end.split(":");
    int startMins = Integer.parseInt(s[0]) * 60 + Integer.parseInt(s[1]);
    int endMins   = Integer.parseInt(e[0]) * 60 + Integer.parseInt(e[1]);
    if (endMins <= startMins) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("End time must be after start time");
    }
}
```

Call it in [createTask](file:///c:/Users/deven/OneDrive/Documents/Desktop/frontend/src/services/task.service.ts#5-9) and [updateTask](file:///c:/Users/deven/OneDrive/Documents/Desktop/frontend/src/services/task.service.ts#13-17):

```java
validateTiming(dto.getStartTime(), dto.getEndTime());
```

